otent, omniscient, omnipresent, eternal, immutable and full of love, justice, goodness, mercy and truth. This is only a representative list of His eternal and unchanging attributes. Although there is only one God, He exists eternally in three persons as the Trinity: the Father, the Son, and the Holy Spirit. We believe these members of the Trinity are coequal in essence, having precisely the same nature, attributes and perfections, but are distinct in subsistence, executing different but harmonious functions. (Mark 12:29, John 4:24, Matt. 3:16-17, Matt. 28:19, 2 Cor. 13:14). \r\n                </p>\r\n              </div>\r\n              <div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n                <h4>JESUS CHRIST</h4>\r\n                <p class=\"text-justify\">We believe that Jesus Christ has existed eternally as the Son of God. At a specific point in time, Jesus became a man (the incarnation) in order to reveal God and redeem humanity. We believe He was supernaturally conceived of the Holy Spirit and born of a virgin, Mary. In His incarnation, He forever possesses both full deity and full humanity in such a way that the properties of each nature are fully retained and undiminished by the union. We believe Jesus died on the cross as a substitute for sinful humanity, was buried, rose bodily from the tomb, ascended into Heaven where He ministers on the behalf of those who have trusted in Him, and someday will come again for His own. (John 1:18, 8:58, Matt. 1:23, Col. 1:15-17, 1 Tim. 1:15, 3:16). \r\n                </p>\r\n              </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n        </section>\r\n        </section>','What We Believe','','inherit','closed','open','','1057-revision-v1','','','2015-08-04 17:52:12','2015-08-04 17:52:12','',1057,'http://www.midtownaustin.org/2015/08/04/1057-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1076,1,'2015-08-04 18:43:08','2015-08-04 18:43:08','<section class=\"parallax parallax-giving\" style=\"background-image: url(https://scontent-dfw1-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xaf1/t31.0-8/s2048x2048/10256695_519143751529359_361980284696071893_o.jpg);\">\r\n    <div class=\"container-fluid\">\r\n        <div class=\"row\">\r\n            <div class=\"container\">\r\n                <div class=\"col-sm-12 text-center\">\r\n                    <h1 title=\"Purpose and Vision of Midtown Church - Central Austin and Campus Ministry\">Purpose &amp; Vision</h1>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n<section>\r\n	<div class=\"container\">\r\n		<div class=\"row\">\r\n			<div class=\"col-md-12 text-center\">\r\n				<h2 class=\"h-lines hl-2\">Midtown Church</h2>\r\n				<p class=\"lead\">A family loved and served by God, compelled to love and serve Austin with God.</p>\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n<section class=\"bg-dark-teal\">\r\n	<div class=\"container\">\r\n		<div class=\"row\">\r\n			<div class=\"col-md-12 text-center\">\r\n				<h2 class=\"h-lines hl-3\">Vision</h2>\r\n				<p class=\"lead\">Our central vision is to glorify God in all things. In that, our more specific vision statement is, \"to see the day when every man, woman and child in Austin hears the gospel from a person who loves them.\"</p>\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n<section class=\"bg-light-gray\">\r\n	<div class=\"container\">\r\n		<div class=\"row\">\r\n			<div class=\"col-sm-3\">\r\n				<img src=\"http://www.midtownaustin.org/wp-content/uploads/love-church-central-austin.jpg\" class=\"img-responsive img-thumbnail\">\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"col-sm-9\">\r\n				<h3>Love</h3>\r\n				<p><strong><em>(Matthew 22:36-40)</em></strong><br>\r\nWe love God because God loved us first. He loved us when we didn’t love Him. He loves us when we fail to love Him. We love Him because he knows everything about us and still loves us. God loves us, therefore we love God.</p>\r\n				<p>We love people because people matter to God. God loves everyone; every man, woman & child. Which means God loves imperfect people like us and so we love imperfect people too. God loves people, therefore we love people.</p>\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n			<div class=\"col-sm-3 col-sm-push-9\">\r\n				serve photo\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"col-sm-9 col-sm-pull-3\">\r\n				<h3>Serve</h3>\r\n				<p><strong><em>(Mark 10:45)</em></strong><br>\r\nJesus came to serve. He gave his life serving. As his followers we chose to use our lives to serve. We chose to serve people who are not like us and who do not like us. We serve people who ask and people who don’t have a voice to ask. We serve the least, the hurting the lonely and the marginalized. We serve because people matter to God. We serve to give people a picture of our God who serves. Jesus came to serve, therefore we are here to serve.</p>\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n			<div class=\"col-sm-3\">\r\n				austin photo\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class=\"col-sm-9\">\r\n				<h3>Austin</h3>\r\n				<p><strong><em>(Jeremiah 29:7)</em></strong><br>\r\n				God has given us a passion for our city; this is where we are called to love & serve.</p>\r\n				<p>We love Austin. We love its culture, its people and its places. As Central Austinites we want to do our part in helping Austin become an even more weird, fun, creative, green and loving city. We hope for a day that every person in Austin has an opportunity to hear about God’s love for them from a friend who loves them.</p>\r\n			</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</section>','Purpose & Vision','','inherit','closed','open','','956-revision-v1','','','2015-08-04 18:43:08','2015-08-04 18:43:08','',956,'http://www.midtownaustin.org/2015/08/04/956-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1077,1,'2015-08-04 18:52:25','2015-08-04 18:52:25','','serving-one-another-in-austin','','inherit','closed','open','','serving-one-another-in-austin','','','2015-08-04 18:52:25','2015-08-04 18:52:25','',956,'http://www.midtownaustin.org