yfully in response to how Jesus has generously served us and to help more people meet Jesus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a community, we take joy in the ways our faith is made stronger through partnering with God serve others. There is a satisfaction that comes from following Jesus’ example of generosity toward those most in need, and it is a privilege to use our resources and time to continue telling God’s story and help bring measurable change in the world. If you are interested in joining a service team email Jake at <a href=\"mailto:jake@midtownaustin.org\">jake@midtownaustin.org</a>.</p>','Sign Up to Serve','We are recuirting for things and stuff and other filler text. It’s awesome. You’re awesome. Be awesomer.','inherit','closed','open','','1091-revision-v1','','','2015-08-21 17:49:43','2015-08-21 17:49:43','',1091,'http://www.midtownaustin.org/2015/08/21/1091-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1340,1,'2015-08-21 17:50:34','2015-08-21 17:50:34','<!-- Page Heading -->\r\n<!-- Parallax Section -->\r\n<section class=\"parallax\" style=\"background-image: url(http://www.midtownaustin.org/wp-content/uploads/midtown-church-page-header-background.jpg);\">\r\n    <div class=\"container-fluid\">\r\n        <div class=\"row\">\r\n            <div class=\"container\">\r\n                <div class=\"text-center\">\r\n                    <h1>Giving &mdash; An Act of Worship</h1>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n</section>\r\n<!-- /.page heading -->\r\n\r\n<!-- Page Content -->\r\n\r\n<section>\r\n    <div class=\"container\">\r\n        <div class=\"row\">\r\n            <div class=\"col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1 text-center\">\r\n                <p class=\"lead\">Jesus is the most generous person who ever lived. He gave his life so that we might live. As Christians, we give our time, talent, and money joyfully in response to Jesus’ generosity and to help more people meet Jesus.</p>\r\n\r\n                <p>As a community, we take joy in the ways our faith is made stronger through giving and receiving together. There is a satisfaction that comes from following Jesus’ example of generosity toward those most in need, and it is a privilege to use our resources and time to continue telling God’s story and help bring measurable change in the world.</p>\r\n\r\n                <p>Below are some ways for you to give to the ministry of Midtown Church.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n<section class=\"bg-light-gray\">\r\n    <div class=\"container\">\r\n        <div class=\"row\">\r\n            <div class=\"col-sm-12 text-center\">\r\n                <h2 class=\"h-lines hl-2\">Ways to Give</h2>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"col-sm-6 text-center\">\r\n                <h2 class=\"h-gray\">Online</h2>\r\n                <p>You can give via credit card or bank withdrawal either one time or recurring. Click the button below to begin.</p>\r\n                <p><a href=\"https://midtownchurch.cloverdonations.com/give/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"btn btn-warning btn-lg\">Click Here to Give Online</a></p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"col-sm-6 text-center\">\r\n                <h2 class=\"h-gray\">Cash &amp; Checks</h2>\r\n                <p>Please make checks payable to Midtown Church and drop them in the offering plate on Sunday or mail to:</p>\r\n                <address>\r\n                    Midtown Church<br>\r\n                    4809 Sinclair Ave<br>\r\n                    Austin, TX 78756\r\n                </address>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n</section>','Give','','inherit','closed','open','','935-revision-v1','','','2015-08-21 17:50:34','2015-08-21 17:50:34','',935,'http://www.midtownaustin.org/2015/08/21/935-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1341,1,'2015-08-21 17:53:57','2015-08-21 17:53:57','<section class=\"parallax\" style=\"background-image: url(http://www.midtownaustin.org/wp-conten